# ============================================
# HOW TO GET YOUR SUPABASE CREDENTIALS:
# ============================================
#
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com and sign in
# 2. Click "New project"
# 3. Give your project a name (e.g., "freshcart")
# 4. Create a secure password
# 5. Select your region (closest to your users)
# 6. Click "Create new project"
#
# 7. Once created, go to "Settings" > "API"
# 8. Copy the "Project URL" and paste it as VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# 9. Copy the "anon public" key and paste it as VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# 10. The database schema will be created automatically when the app starts
#
# ============================================
# YOUR APP IS NOW CONNECTED TO SUPABASE! 🎉
# ============================================

# ============================================
# AUTHENTICATION SETUP (Optional)
# ============================================
#
# Email/Password Authentication is enabled by default in Supabase.
# Users can:
# - Sign up with email and password
# - Sign in with email and password
# - Use magic links for passwordless sign-in
#
# To configure email settings:
# 1. Go to "Authentication" > "Email Templates"
# 2. Customize welcome and recovery emails
#
# ============================================

# ============================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT:
# ============================================
#
# Option 1: Vercel (Recommended)
# - Push code to GitHub
# - Import project in vercel.com
# - Add VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY as environment variables
# - Deploy
#
# Option 2: Netlify
# - Push code to GitHub
# - Import project in netlify.com
# - Add environment variables
# - Deploy
#
# Option 3: Any hosting with static file support
# - Run: npm run build
# - Deploy the 'dist' folder to your hosting
#
# ============================================